<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Calls for Immediate Ceasefire in DRC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The European Union called on
Thursday an immediate cease-fire in the Democratic Republic of
Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
The 15-nation union expressed its grave concern through a
written statement issued by the Austrian presidency.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the ongoing crisis in the DRC and the
wider dangers for the region can only be solved through a
negotiated settlement acceptable to all Congolese that will allow
the DRC and other countries of the region to find peace and
stability.
</P>
<P>
The European Union appreciated and supported the recent
mediation efforts undertaken by South African President Nelson
Mandela in his capacity as chairman of the Southern African
Development Community.
</P>
<P>
The union believes that an immediate cease-fire will be the
precondition for a political process that will lead up to
negotiations aimed at finding a solution to the conflict.
</P>
<P>
The European Union, the statement added, remains ready to help
with the political dialogue and stands ready to support any
negotiation scheme designed to find the consent of all parties
involved.
</P>
<P>
A regional conference, the statement said, can provide the
opportunity for considering issues of a regional dimension and for
creating the mechanism to promote security and cooperation in the
region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
