<HEADLINE> Iranian Deputy FM to Visit Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ameenzadeh will call on Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif and hold
formal talks with Foreign Minister Sartaj Aziz on international,
regional and bilateral issues, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Ameenzadeh's visit follows a recent trip to Iran by Pakistan's
Minister of State for Foreign Affairs Siddique Kahn Kanju.
</P>
<P>
The Afghan issue will prominently figure in the talks as Iran
is highly concerned over the recent offensives of the Taliban
militia in northern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Tension arose between Pakistan and Iran after Iranian diplomats
and a correspondent of Iranian News Agency (IRNA) got missing in
Mazar-i-Sharif early this month when the Taliban captured the
northern Afghan town.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Iran, Kanju renewed Pakistan's offer to
extend cooperation in resolving the diplomatic issue and other
issues. However, media reports have suggested that he failed to
convince the Iranian leadership of Pakistan's role in this regard.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
