<HEADLINE> OAU Central Organ Meets on U.S. Missile Attack on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The central organ of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) mechanism for conflict
prevention, management and resolution held its 51st ordinary
session at ambassadorial level here Thursday on U.S. missile
attack on Sudan.
</P>
<P>
An OAU press release quoted a communique issued by the session
as saying that the meeting which held at the request of the
Sudan, took note of the briefing by the Ambassador of the Sudan
on his country's position on the U.S. cruise missile attack.
</P>
<P>
The central organ expressed its deep concern over the
incident, said the release.
</P>
<P>
It also expressed its strong support to the ongoing efforts of
the African group in New York aimed at securing a meeting of the
U.N. Security Council on the matter and at having the Council
dispatch a fact-finding mission to the Sudan to establish the
facts surrounding the activities of the targeted pharmaceutical
plant in the north of Khartoum, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
The central organ further expressed its grave concern at the
acts of terrorism being perpetrated on the continent such as
those recently carried out in Nairobi and Dar es Salaam with
devastating effects to life and property.
</P>
<P>
The central organ reiterated its strong condemnation of
terrorism in all its forms and called for an urgent collective
international response to the scourge of terrorism which has
become one of the most serious threat to peace and security in
the world. 
</P>
