<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-27 17:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tel Aviv Bombing Injures 21, Leaders Condemn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 27 (Xinhua) -- A total of 21 people were
injured in the explosion in Tel Aviv on Thursday morning, while
both Israeli and Palestinian leaders condemned the bombing attack.
</P>
<P>
The bomb hid in a garbage can went off at an intersection of
the bustling Allenby Street and Rothschild Boulevard. A pregnant
woman and two children were among the injured, one of whom is in
serious condition.
</P>
<P>
The injured have been rushed to hospitals.
</P>
<P>
The explosion erupted during the morning rush hour but it was
lucky that a city public bus carrying passengers just left the
scene before the explosion went off, otherwise, the explosion
could cause more injuries or damage, Israeli police said.
</P>
<P>
No one has claimed responsibility for the bombing, but the
police suspected it to be a terrorist attack.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, who went to Tel Aviv
in the afternoon to see the injured in hospitals, said the
explosion showed the terrorists were acting against Israeli
civilians not only in the West Bank city of Hebron but anywhere.
</P>
<P>
Last week, a Jewish settler was stabbed to death by a
Palestinian in Hebron. Israel has complained that Palestinian
National Authority President Yasser Arafat did not condemn it.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu again urged the Palestinian side to take measures to
fight against all kinds of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
"This attack is another sign that we need to fight terror," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat condemned Thursday's explosion.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting in the West Bank city of Ramallah with
Israeli Labor Knesset (parliament) member Saleh Tarif, Arafat said
the Palestinians condemn any kind of terrorist attacks,
particularly these acts against innocent civilians.
</P>
<P>
Many other people suffered from minor burns to only shock in
the explosion. Tel Aviv police sealed off the area to conduct
investigation immediately after the blast. They found that the
bomb, weighing about one to two pounds, was packed with nails.
</P>
<P>
Police said they will mobilize more personnel to investigate
the incident and vowed to bring the criminals to justice as soon
as possible.
</P>
<P>
Tel Aviv has been a frequent target for Palestinian militants,
led by the Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas), who have been
launching a terror campaign through bombing buses and public
places in order to wreck the Israeli-Palestinian peace process.
</P>
<P>
Israeli security forces have been put on high alert in the past
days following the U.S. missile attacks against suspected Islamic
terrorist-related sites in Sudan and Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Anti-U.S. Islamic activists have warned to launch retaliatory
attacks against American and Israeli targets.
</P>
<P>
Israel is expected to take advantage of the explosion to
pressure the PNA to crack down tougher on militants. David Bar
Illan, Netanyahu's media adviser, said Thursday that the peace
process cannot continue unless Israeli security is secured.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
