<HEADLINE> 9 Million Ethiopian Children to Be Inoculated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Ministry of
Health said Thursday that about nine million children under the
age of five will be vaccinated against poliomyelitis in polio
immunization campaigns to be launched in two rounds in October
and November.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted Hiwot Mengistu, children
health care team leader of the ministry as saying the
immunization campaigns will be carried out at 32 vaccination
stations across the nation and more than 31,000 health
professionals and 62,206 volunteers will take part in the
campaigns.
</P>
<P>
All the necessary medicament useful for the campaigns are
being imported to the country, said Hiwot.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has plans to eradicate polio by the year 2000. Over
eight million children were inoculated against the disease last
year.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,000 children are infected with the virus that causes
polio each year in the country. 
