<HEADLINE> New Study Shows Record Numbers Online </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles, August 27 (Xinhua) -- A new survey by Nielsen
Media this week shows that more people in the United States and
Canada are online and doing their shopping there.
</P>
<P>
The number of Internet users older than 16 in the two countries
reached 79 million as of June, according to the study. That's 36
percent increase over last year, when a survey showed 58 million
users online.
</P>
<P>
Of the 79 million Net users, Nielsen said, 20 million are
buying products and services online. And the number of Web
shoppers -- people checking out or comparing products and services
on the Web -- is now 48 million.
</P>
<P>
"The Internet continues its impressive growth as a
communications, research, entertainment and commercial medium,"
said Jerome Samson, director of technology and business strategy
at Nielsen in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Based on the statistics, he said, the number of Internet users
grew at a rate of 2.5 percent a month from January 1997 through
June this year. When it came to e-commerce, the numbers grew at
3.5 percent a month from January 1997 through September 1997. And
from September through June this year, the growth in online buyers
accelerated 8 percent a month.
</P>
<P>
"The dramatic increase in online purchasing is primarily due to
people realizing how quick and easy it is to shop on the Web,"
Samson said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
