<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 16:00 GMT, August 28 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL -- The South Korean government Friday announced the
suspension of credit to weak and nonviable subsidiaries of the
nation's five biggest conglomerates from next month.
</P>
<P>
In his report to the National Assembly on Thursday, Lee
Hun-jai, chairman of the Financial Supervisory Commission, said
any subsidiaries of Hyundai, Daewoo, Samsung, LG and SK, which had
lost competitiveness would be subjected to the credit suspension.
(SKorea-Credit Suspension)
</P>
