<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Machinery Exports Hit by Steep Drop in New Orders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The German machine-building
industry suffered a 15 percent steep drop in foreign orders in
July mainly due to the Asian financial crisis and declining
investments in Latin America, the industry said Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the German machine-building industry association
VDMA in Frankfurt, the sharp drop in foreign orders wiped out a
six percent gain in domestic orders, so that the industry saw an
overall drop of seven percent in new orders in July.
</P>
<P>
A positive development came only from Western Europe where
orders for German investment goods increased by seven percent in
July over the same month of last year, the VDMA said.
</P>
<P>
The association, however, also expressed the belief that the
steep drop in foreign orders in July was partly exaggerated by the
extraordinarily high order volume registered in July last year.
</P>
<P>
For the period from May to July, the German machine-building
industry only received two percent less foreign orders than the
same period of last year, the VDMA said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
