the Beijiang river at the Feilaixia water conservation project was
completed.
</P>
<P>
Feilaixia is the largest water conservation project in south
China's Guangdong province since 1949 and a comprehensive flood,
electricity, shipping, cultivation, tourism and water supply
project. It will control over 70 percent of the Beijiang's
drainage area and have a capacity of 1.9 billion cubic meters and
installed generating capacity of 140,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that Feilaixia will increase the flood protection
of Guangdong, especially in the Pearl River Delta.
</P>
