<HEADLINE> Funcinpec Reaffirms Rejection of Election Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's Funcinpec party
said Friday that the National Election Committee (NEC) and
Constitutional Council must resolve all complaints concerning the
general election before it accepted the result and offered to
cooperate.
</P>
<P>
In a four-point statement released Friday, the Funcinpec party,
led by Prince Norodom Ranariddh, said it could not accept the
result because of widespread voting and counting irregularities.
</P>
<P>
According to the official figures, Hun Sen's Cambodian People's
Party (CPP) won 41.4 percent of the vote, while his main
opponents, Funcinpec and the Sam Rainsy Party, received 31.7
percent and 14.3 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
But Funcinpec and the Sam Rainsy Party have rejected the count
since the release of the preliminary result.
</P>
<P>
"The preliminary result of the General Election on July 26
announced by the NEC did not reflect the will of the Cambodian
people," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
"Funcinpec and other political parties had filed complaints to
the NEC and demanded that the voting and counting irregularities,
and the illegally used formula allocating assembly seats be
properly investigated. However, the NEC had rejected most of the
complaints," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Funcinpec was striving to seek compromises in order to resolve
the main issues in the best interests of the Cambodian people and
the country, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The two parties have held large protests in front of the
National Assembly. They also demanded Second Prime Minister Hun
Sen step down as the condition to forming a new coalition with the
his party which won the election, but fell short of the two-thirds
majority to form a government alone.
</P>
<P>
The NEC would likely delay the scheduled announcement on August
29 of official election results until several days' later, said
some officials, leaving time for the Constitutional Council to
hold public hearings on fraud complaints. 
</P>
</TEXT>
