<HEADLINE> Hong Kong New Airport Operating Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The new Hong Kong
International Airport is running smoothly in both passenger and
cargo services, the Airport Authority (AA) said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Passenger services at Chek Lap Kok have reached levels of
efficiency equal to or better than at the old Kai Tak.
</P>
<P>
Over the past week, eight out of ten flights were leaving on
time or within 15 minutes of schedule, almost all arriving
passengers were clearing immigration within 15 minutes, and the
average waiting time for claiming their baggage was about ten
minutes, said AA, which oversees the operation of the airport.
</P>
<P>
The two air cargo franchisees at the new airport also made
progress, handling a total of 4,800 tons of cargoes daily. Hong
Kong Air Cargo Terminals Limited has resumed full operation at its
Super Terminal One at Chek Lap Kok, processing 3,800 tons a day,
while the other operator Asia Airfreight Terminal handles 1,000
tons. 
</P>
