<HEADLINE> China's Legislature to Vote On Two Laws And Treasury Bond Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The National People's Congress
Standing Committee, China's top legislature, is expected to vote
on a draft of a higher education law and amendments to the land
management law tomorrow and will decide whether to ratify a State
Council bill on 100 billion yuan in treasury bonds.
</P>
<P>
The Committee heard proposed changes in the two laws and a
report from the NPC's Financial and Economic Committee.
</P>
<P>
A suggestion of legislators that Party committees are leaders
of universities, but should not handle all work, like that of
university presidents and that they should support those
presidents in their duties in a responsible and independent way
was added and the duties of Party committees and university
presidents was clarified in the draft.
</P>
<P>
They also said that misuse of land and deforestation are part
of the reason for the devestating floods on the Yangtze River and
suggested a new draft of the land management law prohibiting
wasteland caused by deforestation, filling and leveling of lakes
and cultivating rivers.
</P>
<P>
The NPC Financial and Economic Committee suggested that the
legislature approve a State Council bill on 100 billion yuan worth
of treasury bonds, calling it feasible because of deflation and
too much currency having been taken out of circulation.  
