<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asian Games Attract Enough Sponsors: Organizers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Games to be held in
December has attracted enough sponsorship to finance the event,
organizers said here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Bangkok Asian Games Organising Committee Financial
Director Santipab Thejavanijaya said: "The marketing promotion
for the Games has been quite successful."
</P>
<P>
Organizers said they had been seeking 100 million U.S. dollars
to stage the December Games and had gone way beyond that target.
</P>
<P>
So far 85 million U.S. dollars had been raised from 11 key
sponsors, they said.
</P>
<P>
Organizers added the events would be televised to 43 countries
and regions to an expected audience of three billion viewers.
</P>
<P>
Santipab said the organizing committee would also bring in
some 320 million baht from ticket sales during the games.
</P>
<P>
The organizing committee said that all the sports facilities
would be completed well before the Games, which will be held from
December 6 to 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
