<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President on Diplomatic Work (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here today that China will make efforts to create a better
international environment favorable to the realization of the
country's goals in its socialist moderization drive.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks while addressing China's envoys at a
national meeting on diplomatic work.
</P>
<P>
To that end, Jiang said, China will implement the
diplomatic ideas of late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping,
unswervingly adhere to an independent foreign policy of peace,
and implement the principles set forth by the 15th Congress of
the Communist Party of China, thus bringing the country's diplomatic
work into the next century.
</P>
<P>
Other Chinese leaders including Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li
Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing, all members of
the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee, also met with delegates attending the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he considered this meeting, held on the eve of the
new century, important for China's diplomatic work. "After the
previous envoy meeting held in 1993, China's diplomacy scored new
achievements," he said, adding that those efforts helped keep a
good neighborly and international environment for the country.
</P>
<P>
In his address, the president summed up achievements including
the improvement of relationships with all major countries; the
important turnaround in Sino-U.S.ties; enhanced solidarity and
cooperation between China and other developing countries; the
successful resumption of the exercise of China's sovereignty over
Hong Kong; the improvement of the situation across the Taiwan
Straits, and ongoing multi-lateral diplomacy.
</P>
<P>
"China's international position has been upgraded, with greater
influence in international affairs," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Jiang attributed this progress to adherence to the diplomatic
thoughts of late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping. "Applying the
viewpoints of dialectic and historical materialism, Deng calmly
observed the drastic changes in the international arena and made a
series of scientific conclusions and decisions based on his
objective analysis of the development trends and characteristics
of the contemporary world and the world situation," Jiang pointed
out.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
