<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Propose Int'l Conference on Monetary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia will table a proposal
calling on the international society to hold an international
conference on monetary and financial concerns, Foreign Minister
Ali Alatas said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
This proposal has been made sometime ago but developed nations
refused to hold such a conference because they thought the World
Bank and the International Monetary Fund (IMF) are already there,
said the minister when talking about the forthcoming Non-Aligned
Movement (NAM) Summit to be held in Durban, South Africa from
August 29 to September 3.
</P>
<P>
Given the fact that the monetary crisis continues to plague
East and Southeast Asia, Indonesia considers that such a
conference is important, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the field of politics, he said, Indonesia will also propose
to the Movement the formation of a special mission to countries
sponsoring the Middle East peace process, like the United States
and Russia.
</P>
<P>
The special mission needs to meet with Palestinian President
Yasser Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, the
minister said.
</P>
<P>
Alatas said that the NAM needs to play a more active role in
the Middle East, particularly in settling the problems related to
Israel's move to continue the development of human settlements in
areas it is occupies.
</P>
<P>
Alatas, who was appointed to lead the Indonesian delegation to
the NAM summit, said President B.J. Habibie will not be able to
attend the summit because of the vacancy in the post of vice
president who should take over his state duties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980828.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President On Diplomatic Work (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang pointed to Deng Xiaoping's ideas on diplomacy as a guide
to long-term diplomacy in China, and said that an in-depth study
of Deng's ideas accords with global changes and whether China can
succeed in teamwork in diplomacy depends on it.
</P>
<P>
Deng was not only a great statesman and strategist, but also a
outstanding diplomat with good diplomatic ideas and artistry and
a distinctive style, he said.
</P>
<P>
Deng's ideas are an important part of Deng Xiaoping Theory,
which is a combination of Marxism-Leninism and Chinese diplomatic
practices and a development of Mao Zedong Thought in a new
historical period, Jiang explained.
</P>
<P>
He said the world is heading toward multi-polarization now that
the Cold War has ended, and international tensions have gradually
eased, with significant changes in international relations and
progress.
</P>
<P>
This trend helps to limit hegemony and power politics and is
conducive to a new international political and economic order with
justice and fairness, and brings a peaceful, stable and prosperous
world into the new century. But, he said, there will be a
considerably long period of evolution before a new global pattern
is formed eventually.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Jiang also pointed out that the economic
globalization is arousing wide attention. Economic globalization,
is an objective and irreversible trend in the development of
the world economy, he said.
</P>
<P>
In today's world, no one country developing economically can
cut itself off from the rest of the world, he said, noting: "We
need to continue the opening-up policy and adapt ourselves to
economic globalization."
</P>
<P>
He asked everyone to participate in international economic
cooperation and competition and to make full use of opportunities
and challenges that come with globalization, while keeping alert
to the risks brought by globalization, and to work independently
and minimize risks to maintain economic safety and better develop
the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980828.0094 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President on Diplomatic Work (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang stressed that in terms of the global situation at the
turn of the century, there are generally more opportunities and
hopes than challenges and difficulties, and more favorable factors
than unfavorable ones.
</P>
<P>
"We must have a clear understanding of the main stream of
development, seize opportunities, and strive for a more positive
and favorable position for our nation in the international
competition of the 21st century," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that the primary task for China's diplomatic
work is to create a peaceful environment for the country's
socialist modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
China's reform, opening-up and modernization drive need a
domestic political situation of stability and unity, as well
as a peaceful international environment, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence,
China should properly handle relations with other major nations to
promote global multi-polarization, he noted.
</P>
<P>
China should adhere to the principle of seeking friendly
relationship with all neighboring nations, and properly handle
relations with them, the leader said.
</P>
<P>
He added that China will further strengthen solidarity and
cooperation with all other developing countries, and make
concerted efforts with them to safeguard the rights and interests
of all developing countries.
</P>
<P>
China will actively participate in multi-lateral diplomatic
activities, firmly safeguard its own sovereignty, territorial
integrity and national dignity, and work hard to advance the great
cause of the reunification of the motherland, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that China must take a clear-cut stand,
always uphold principles, work effectively and wage necessary
struggles when dealing with issues related to state sovereignty,
national security and fundamental interests, to the rights and
interests of developing countries, to world peace and regional
stability, and to the establishment of a new global political and
economic order that is just, fair and rational.
</P>
</TEXT>
