<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President on Diplomatic Work (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that new situations and tasks make higher
demands on China's diplomatic work and the building of the
diplomatic ranks.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes people working in the diplomatic field stick to
the ideology of "emancipating the mind, and seeking truth from
facts," and bear Deng Xiaoping Theory, especially his
diplomatic thoughts, in mind.
</P>
<P>
He further hopes they will learn to acquire a correct
understanding of the international situation by observing and
analyzing it with the Marxist stand, method and viewpoint.
</P>
<P>
He said that people in the diplomatic field should
maintain a firm political belief and stance, foster keen
political insight and judgement, and observe and
analyze the world situation from an overall political view.
</P>
<P>
"You must implement the principles and policies of the Central
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party conscientiously and
creatively," Jiang stressed.
</P>
<P>
"You must inherit and carry forward the fine style and
tradition of diplomatic work advocated by Mao Zedong, Zhou Enlai
and Deng Xiaoping," he added.
</P>
<P>
"You must firmly establish a correct view of the world, life
and values, and stand the tests of various international
environments and turmoils," he continued.
</P>
<P>
Leaders at all levels should place emphasis on the building of
diplomatic contingents, and put the cultivation of young people in
an important position in order to have more people demonstrate
their talents and guarantee a powerful organization for the new
phase of our diplomatic work, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
The meeting's aims were the following:
</P>
<P>
-- To study Deng Xiaoping Theory;
</P>
<P>
-- To implement the guideline of the CPC National Congress;
</P>
<P>
-- To analyze the profound changes in the world situation;
</P>
<P>
-- To summarize the fresh experience in diplomatic work;
</P>
<P>
-- To put forward the main target and tasks in cross-century
diplomatic work; and
</P>
<P>
-- To further open up a new phase for China's diplomatic work;
</P>
<P>
Attending the meeting were all of China's diplomats stationed
abroad and several consuls general.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, which began on August 24, NPC Standing
Committee Chairman Li Peng held a panel discussion with some of the
diplomats.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji delivered an important report on the current
situation in the battle against the floods and China's
economy. Vice-Premier Qian Qichen delivered a report on the
current international situation and promotion of the reunification
of the motherland. Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan also gave a work
report.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is scheduled to close tomorrow.  
</P>
</TEXT>
