<HEADLINE> Heidelberg Plans to Double Asia Turnover by 2003 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Heidelberger Druckmaschinen Ag
(Heidelberg) of Germany, the world's largest supplier in printing
systems, continues to regard Asia as a market with enormous
potential and plans to increase its market shares substantially in
this region.
</P>
<P>
Hartmut Mehdorn, chairman of the Heidelberg Executive Board,
told reporters at a press conference here Friday that the
company's goal is to double its Asia Turnover to 1.6 billion DM
(882 million U.S. dollars) by 2003.
</P>
<P>
Heidelberg recently took over all the sales companies and
activities for graphics products from the Danish firm East Asiatic
Company Ltd. A/S (EAC), Copenhagen, for about 465 million DM (256
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Heidelberg has already set up its headquarters in Beijing,
Shanghai, Guangzhou and Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Heidelberg is currently represented in about 170 countries and
exports 82 percent of its products.
</P>
<P>
In the 1997/98 fiscal year which ended on March 31, this year,
the company recorded a turnover of around 6.8 billion DM (3.78
billion U.S. dollars).  
</P>
