<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Vows to Stop Deforestation in Yangtze, Yellow River Basins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, Augest 28 (Xinhua) -- China today vowed to stop
deforestation in the Yangtze and Yellow river basins to
avoid flooding and improve the environment.
</P>
<P>
According to Li Yucai, Vice-Director of the State Forestry
Administration, deforestation on the upper reaches of the
country's major rivers was one of the reasons for the current
series of floods hitting China.
</P>
<P>
He said that the state this year will invest 3.12 billion yuan
(380 million U.S. dollars) in infrastructure, and 3 billion yuan
in special loans and financial allocations in the protection of
forest resources.
</P>
<P>
During a working conference which closed today, he also urged
forestry departments at all levels to take immediate action to
prepare for a nationwide forest-protection project.
</P>
<P>
"We will give first priority to the protection of
forests," the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
