<DOCNO> XIE19980828.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Super Train Put into Cross-border Service in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 28 (Xinhua) -- A double-deck electric train
of the Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation (KCRC) started
cross-border operation on Friday, shuttling passengers faster than
ever between Hong Kong and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The state-of-the-art KCRC Through Train, or KTT, is the first
electric train to run cross-border trips. Twelve double-deck
coaches offer "airline-style" seating, video screens and fold-out
tables, and twin locomotives propel the train, cutting the
110-minute trip by about 15 minutes.
</P>
<P>
At the launching ceremony Friday morning, K. Y. Yeung, chairman
and chief executive of KCRC, said KTT marked a milestone in the
through train services between Hong Kong and Guangdong province,
which were introduced in 1979.
</P>
<P>
Its operation is also of great significance to KCRC itself as
KTT is the first through train owned and managed by the company,
Yeung added. Previously all through trains to Guangdong Province
were run by Guangzhou Railway.
</P>
<P>
On the same day of KTT's maiden trip, Guangzhou Railway will
put its Xinshisu (New Speed) electric train into service.
</P>
<P>
The two pairs of trains will each make a return trip daily,
bringing the number of Hong Kong-Guangzhou through trains to four
pairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
