<HEADLINE> China's Air Quality in Cities Improves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- China's air quality in cities has
become better over the past week and most cities enjoyed good air
quality, according to the China Environmental Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
The center's latest air-quality report said that from August 21
to 27, eleven cities -- Shantou, Nanning, Fuzhou, Zhuhai, Guilin,
Ningbo, Wenzhou, Xiamen, Zhanjiang, Haikou and Beihai -- enjoyed
excellent air quality.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-nine cities, including Shanghai, Nanjing, Tianjin and
Hangzhou, reported good air quality.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, Guangzhou, Xi'ning, Chongqing, Jinan and Lanzhou
suffered from slight air pollution over the past week, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The major problem in Beijing and Guangzhou was high levels of
nitrogen oxide. Chongqing suffered from high levels of sulphur
dioxide and Xi'ning, Jinan and Lanzhou reported high levels of
suspended particles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
