<HEADLINE> Large Coal Gas Field Discovered in Northern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- A large coal gas field, covering
an area of 1,200 sq km and with potential a gas reserve of 200
billion cubic meters, has been discovered in north China's Shanxi
Province, according to sources from the Ministry of Land and
Natural Resources.
</P>
<P>
After two years of exploration, China United Coal Gas
Corporation Ltd. discovered the field in the southeastern
region of the province.
</P>
<P>
Three pits in the province's Tunliu County are expected to
produce more than 5,000 cubic meters of gas daily. And another
seven pits that the corporation plans to mine are estimated to
have a daily capacity of 10,000 cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
The gas field, located within 200 km of large cities such as
Changzhi and Jincheng cities in Shanxi Province, and Zhengzhou and
Luoyang in Henan Province, will bring great social and economic
benefits to the region, according to the corporation.
</P>
<P>
The corporation said they plan to verify 300 sq km of the field
and ascertain gas reserves of 54 billion cubic meters by the end
of this year. They also plan to construct a coal gas field with an
annual capacity of one-billion cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate that if the field is completely verified, the
annual production capacity could reach four-billion cubic meters.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
