<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 28 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques
Chirac and French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin sent solidarity
messages respectively Thursday to their South African
counterparts following Tuesday's deadly bombing in Cape Town.
</P>
<P>
In a message to President Nelson Mandela, Chirac expressed his
"dismay" and "heartfelt solidarity" and requested Mandela to
convey his "deepest sympathy to the victims families".
</P>
