have learnt with emotion the attack perpetrated yesterday evening
in Cape Town which caused the death of one person and wounded
many others."
</P>
<P>
Conveying his condolences on behalf of the French government,
Jospin stressed: "France stays mobilized, together with the
international community, to fight all aspects of terrorism, which
can hit every one of us."
</P>
<P>
The bombing in a U.S.-franchised restaurant in Cape Town was
suspected to be linked to U.S. missile strikes against alleged
Muslim terrorists in Sudan and Afghanistan last week. 
