<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Great Wall Cultural Festival Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Great Wall Cultural and Art
Festival opened here today at famous Juyongguan Pass in Changping
County, north of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Many tourists from around the world attended the opening
ceremony and enjoyed gala performances by a host of noted Chinese
artists.
</P>
<P>
Today's special entertainment program included setting off the
watchtower smoke and a performance by actors in ancient warrior
dress, attracting thousands of spectators.
</P>
<P>
Cultural and artistic events including open-air concerts,
painting exhibitions, a handicraft fair, and opera, martial arts
and acrobatic performances are scheduled throughout the festival
from August 28 to October 8.
</P>
<P>
The Juyongguan Pass, a section of the Great Wall in Beijing
Municipality, has become a new tourist attraction since it was
opened to the public in March.  
</P>
</TEXT>
