<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank of China Restructures Overseas Investment Bank Branch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China International
Holding Co. Ltd. (BOCI) moved its head office from London to
Hong Kong today, marking a successful ending to the Bank of
China's restructuring of its overseas investment business.
</P>
<P>
The BOCI, formerly a London-based investment banking subsidiary
of the Bank of China, is expected to take over the bank's overseas
investment business following this move to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
This restructuring will set up a series of specialized branch
companies under the BOCI, including BOC Group Trustee Co. Ltd.,
BOCI Asia Ltd., BOCI Capital Ltd., BOCI Asset Management Ltd.,
BOCI Investment Ltd., BOCI Research Ltd., BOCI Direct Investment
Management Ltd. and BOCI Securities Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The BOC expects that the restructured BOCI will develop into a
top regional investment bank in Hong Kong, specializing in
securities, financial consulting, mergers, asset management,
project financing, syndicated loans and direct investing.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of China International also vows to extend full
support to the domestic enterprise reform program by restructuring
state-owned enterprises and helping them raise funds on the
overseas capital market.
</P>
<P>
Opening at a time when the Asian economy is badly shattered by
the Asian financial crisis, and the international investment
banking sector faces severe challenges, the Bank of China
International will signal to the world the strong confidence the
BOC has in the Hong Kong market and its future.
</P>
<P>
Before the restructuring effort, the BOC was involved in a wide
range of investment banking ventures in Hong Kong including
securities placement, underwriting, securities trading, direct
investing and asset management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
