<HEADLINE> Macao Unemployment Rate Reaches Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate between May
and July in Macao reached 4.7 percent, a record high over the past
eight years.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
on Friday show that there were about 10,000 people out of job.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate was 0.5 percent higher than the
April-June period, and 1.4 percent higher than the May-July
period.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the underemployment rate was recorded at 1.4
percent, up 0.5 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Vitor Pessoa, secretary for economic and coordination, told the
Macao Daily News on Thursday that the government is to review its
current policy on the import of foreign laborers, and will
probably reduce the import number to ease the pressure of
unemployment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
