<HEADLINE> Macao Population Reaches New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Macao's resident population
reached 425,100 by the end of June, up about 3,000 from the end of
last year, latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Census and Statistics Department made the estimate in
a release on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Macao's total land area added up to about 23 square kilometers,
and its residents mainly live in the peninsula instead of its two
islands.
</P>
<P>
The increase of population was mainly the result of more
births. While there were 1,036 recorded births between April and
June, only 359 people died in the period.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the number of legal immigrants from China's
mainland reached 168 between April and June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
