<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Timepiece Export Steady </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The export of watches and
clocks in Hong Kong remained steady in the first five months of
the year despite the unfavorable international trading environment
brought about by the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference Friday, Co-chairman of the Hong
Kong Watch and Clock Fair '98 Clement Cheuk said the Asian
financial crisis has undermined Hong Kong's exports of watches and
clocks to the region.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, strong economy in the United States and
noticeable growth in the European Union help to offset the decline
in exports to Asian markets.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of the year, total exports of Hong
Kong's watches and clocks rose by 9 percent to the United States
and 11 percent to the EU, according to Cheuk.
</P>
<P>
In the same period, exports of timepiece from Hong Kong to
China's mainland and Japan, Hong Kong's second and third largest
timepiece buyers, registered decreases of 6 percent and 3 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
He added that Latin America and Eastern Europe have become
potential markets for Hong Kong companies.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that Hong Kong's total export of clocks and
watches in the first five months of the year remained basically at
the same level as that of last year.
</P>
<P>
Wong Hung Fai, also co-chairman of the fair, said Hong Kong
timepiece manufacturers should no longer concentrate on low to
medium-end products in the face of competition from other Asian
countries.
</P>
<P>
"They have to move up market to produce high quality and
value-added items, and should also put emphasis on design and
production technology in order to maintain Hong Kong's position as
a leading producer of watches and clocks in the world," he said.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Hong Kong scored a total timepiece export value of
46.8 billion HK dollars (6 billion U.S. dollars, including
domestic export and re-export).
</P>
<P>
According to the organizers, this year the Hong Kong Watch and
Clock Fair, scheduled for September 9 to 13, has attracted 808
timepiece companies from 15 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Exhibits will include all kinds of innovative watches and
clocks, related parts and components, as well as tools and
machinery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
