<HEADLINE> Pak FM Leaves for South Africa on Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Foreign Minister
Sartaj Aziz will leave here for Durban, South Africa on Saturday
to attend the ministerial level meeting of the 12th Non-Aligned
Movement (NAM) summit, officials said Friday.
</P>
<P>
This will be the maiden overseas trip of Aziz as foreign
minister, who shifted from the post of finance minister to the
current one early this month.
</P>
<P>
The ministerial level meeting of NAM is expected to finalize
the agenda of the summit which is scheduled for Monday.
</P>
<P>
Aziz is expected to submit Pakistan's proposals for the summit
agenda, which focus on the Kashmir issue and the establishment of
peace in the South Asian region.
</P>
<P>
Aziz will also meet his counterparts from some other countries,
to brief them on Pakistan's position on regional and international
issues, according to the officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
