<HEADLINE> UK PM Blair Urges Russia to Stick to Reform Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 28 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony
Blair Friday urged the Russian government to stick to its reform
program in an effort to take the country out of the current
financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Russian financial situation continues worsening with the
Russian rouble going into a free-fall triggered by Russian Central
Bank's suspension of all foreign exchange trading.
</P>
<P>
Blair said in a BBC Radio interview Friday morning: "It is a
very serious situation in Russia, there's no doubt about that at
all. The only answer and response to it is to carry on with the
process of reforms."
</P>
<P>
"That is the only way for Russia to get out of the financial and
economic difficulties that it has," Blair said, adding: "The
program and plan that has been put together over a long period of
time by the international institutions does genuinely offer the only
way out of this."
</P>
<P>
In other developments, Blair had a brief phone conversation with
U.S. President Bill Clonton Thursday night, exchanging views
on the Russian economic situation and Clinton's coming visit to
Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
