<HEADLINE> Zambia, Zimbabwe Trade Imbalance to End: Chiluba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The imbalance in bilateral trade
between Zambia and Zimbabwe will soon be normalized following a
series of discussions between the two countries, Zambian
President Frederich Chiluba said.
</P>
<P>
President Chiluba disclosed this Thursday in Lusaka before his
departure for a three-day state visit to Zimbabwe at the
invitation of his Zimbabwean counterpart Robert Mugabe.
</P>
<P>
The Zambia Daily Mail newspaper Friday quoted Chiluba as
saying that there are a lot of discussions between the two
nations and he hopes an "amicable" solution would be found soon.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, the Zambian government and industrial
sectors have been accusing Zimbabwe and South Africa of turning
Zambia into a dumping ground, and urging the play ground must be
evened.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba is very optimistic about the future of the bilateral
trade and believes that the trade imbalance between Zambia and
Zimbabwe would end soon.
</P>
<P>
"Things are moving very well and I am very hopeful that the
anomalies will be rectified soon," said the Zambian leader.
</P>
</TEXT>
