<HEADLINE> Another Five Large Russian Banks Merge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Another five large Russian
banks led by the National Reserve Bank (NRB) have merged into a
new group, the Itar-Tass news agency reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The group comprises NRB, Inkombank, Avtobank, Mezhcombank and
Alpha-Bank, the NRB press service was cited as saying.
</P>
<P>
NRB Board Chairman Alexander Lebedev was elected chairman of
the council of representatives of the new banking group.
</P>
<P>
It is the second major banking merger after Russian president
Boris Yeltsin dismissed Sergei Kiriyenko's government on August 23.
</P>
<P>
The first merger took place on Tuesday, involving Uneximbank,
Most Bank and MENATEP. 
</P>
