<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were killed and two
others seriously wounded in a car crash in suburban Maputo
Thursday night, a Mozambican national newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Noticias said that the two light-scale vehicles
collided on the super highway between capital Maputo and Matola
Town.
</P>
<P>
The victims were immediately sent to the nearby hospitals, and
some of them were passers-by, said fire brigade members who had
rushed to rescue.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the incident was not known yet.
</P>
<P>
The 25-kilometer super highway is one of the few expressways
in the southern African country. However, it has been called "the
corridor of death" because of frequent traffic accidents.
</P>
