<HEADLINE> Anti-Drug Exhibition Ends in Southwest China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition fully displaying
the major anti-drug achievements in southwest China's Yunnan
Province over the past 16 years, ended today after being on
display for six months.
</P>
<P>
Starting in the provincial capital of Kunming, the exhibition
toured the province's 12 cities and hosted more than 700,000
visitors.
</P>
<P>
By displaying some 1,000 photos and a large number of
objects seized by local police, the exhibition demonstrated the
firm anti-drug determination of the province, which borders the
notorious "Golden Triangle."
</P>
<P>
Since 1982, when the province began its anti-drug efforts, local
police have cracked more than 50,000 drug cases and confiscated over
70 tons of drugs, 80 percent of the country's total. 
</P>
