<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980828.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistani PM Announces Quran Shall Be Supreme Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif Friday announced that the Holy Quran and Sunnah shall be
the supreme law in the country.
</P>
<P>
The 15th constitutional amendment bill is being introduced in
the parliament for the purpose, Sharif told the nation in a live
radio-television address in the National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Delivering the epoch-making speech, the prime minister said
that the decision would change the social fabric of the society
and lay a solid foundation for eliminating crimes, corruption and
malpractice -- which had crept into the society like "a rampant
cancer."
</P>
<P>
"A surgery of this cancer is urgently required," he said.
</P>
<P>
The historic decision today, he said, would help in
establishing an Islamic social welfare state "which is the main
objective of our independence."
</P>
<P>
According to some constitutional experts, all courts will be
bound to decide cases according to the Quran and Sunnah after the
passage of the constitutional amendment in the two houses of the
parliament.
</P>
<P>
A two-third majority in the Senate and the National Assembly is
required to pass the amendment. The government will get it passed
in the National Assembly easily, but face problems in the Senate
as it does not enjoy a majority there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980828.0206 </DOCNO>
