<HEADLINE> Third Flood Crest on Songhua River Passes Jiamusi City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The third flood peak on the
Songhua River passed Jiamusi City in northeast China's
Heilongjiang Province this morning.
</P>
<P>
This latest crest stood at 80.34 meters, had a flow rate of
16,200 cubic meters per second, and was the second strongest the
city has seen since 1960.
</P>
<P>
The water level then dropped to 80.32 meters, still 1.32 meters
above the danger mark, and the flow rate dropped to 16,100 cubic
meters per second.
</P>
<P>
Experts believe the water will remain high for more than 20
days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
