<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Iranian deputy foreign
minister Mohsin Ameenzadeh arrived here Friday on a one-day visit
for talks with Pakistani officials on the Afghan issue, officials
said.
</P>
<P>
The visit follows a recent trip to Iran by Pakistani State
Minister for Foreign Affairs Siddique Khan Kanju.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian official will meet Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif and
hold formal talks with Foreign Minister Sartaj Aziz on
international, regional and bilateral issues, focusing on
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
He is likely to bring a special message from Iranian President
Muhammad Khatami for Prime Minister Sharif, they said.
</P>
<P>
Tension emerged between Pakistan and Iran after Iranian
diplomats went missing in northern Afghanistan when the Islamic
Taliban captured Mazar-e-Sharif, headquarters of the anti-Taliban
alliance, early this month.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan recognizes the Taliban regime while Iran accepts the
northern alliance led by former Afghan president Burhannuddin
Rabbani. 
</P>
</TEXT>
