<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand's Beach Volleyball Aims High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PATTAYA, THAILAND, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's men's
beach volleyball team stands a very good chance to win gold in
the upcoming 13th Asian Games, the team's Australian head coach
Ken Breen told Xinhua Friday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua at the beach volleyball venue for
the Games, located in the famous beach resort city, Breen said
levels are even among men's beach volleyball teams in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Thailand may face challenges from Indonesia and Japan, but is
very likely to win a gold thanks to its four tough players and
good athletes management and training, he said.
</P>
<P>
As for the women's teams in Asia, the Australian said China,
Japan, Thailand and Indonesia are the four strongest.
</P>
<P>
It is possible for Thai girls to beat China and Japan and win
a bronze medal in the Asian Games, he said. But that will depend
on the group drawing and the girls' performance during the Games,
he added.
</P>
<P>
When asked about the unfavorable heights of both men and women
players, he said height is not the most important element in
beach volleyball since only one player will perform the block.
</P>
<P>
"Speed and tactic will compensate that," he said.
</P>
<P>
The players have advantages over their opponents since they
are training five hours a day and six days a week at the place
where the formal matches will be held and get familiar to the
wind and tide there.
</P>
<P>
Besides, as weather in countries like China and Japan are
getting cold, athletes there will pass their peak, while the Thai
players will continue training to reach their peak in December.
</P>
<P>
Before the Asian Games, both men's and women's teams will
participate in dozens of matches, including the Singapore Open.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Australian beach volleyball teams will come to
Thailand in November to help the Thais' training.
</P>
<P>
"Beach volleyball may become one of the successes of Thailand
in the Asian Games," Breen said in confidence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
