<HEADLINE> Mercury Beats Comets in WNBA Finals Game 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Jennifer Gillom blocked a
shot and netted the winning basket to help the Phoenix Mercury
win over the defending champion Houston Comets 54-51 in Game 1 of
the WNBA Finals on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Gillom's winner came with 8.9 seconds remaining after she got
a pass from Michele Timms. WNBA Most Valuable Player Cynthia
Cooper, who scored 31 points, miss a 28-foot shot at the buzzer.
It was the fourth loss for the Comets, who were tipped as the hot
favorite to defend their title.
</P>
<P>
The best-of-3 series shifts to Houston on Saturday and Game 3,
if needed, will be Tuesday night in Houston.
</P>
<P>
Gillom scored 15 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, and Griffiths
had a career-high 12 rebounds and eight points. Sheryl Swoopes
had 11 rebounds and eight points for the Comets, who were 27-3 in
the regular season.
</P>
<P>
The Mercury were 19-11 during the season, and their playoff
with Cleveland were stretched to three games. The team led 33-29
at halftime, but in the final five minutes, the lead was changed
hands three times.
</P>
<P>
Cooper, who was selected into All-WNBA lineup, had 16 points
in the first half, while the Mercury made only four of their
first 15 shots. 
</P>
