<HEADLINE> About 3,000 Forces to Ensure Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Around 3,000 police and
military police will ensure safety during the opening and closing
ceremonies of the Asian Games, according to a Thai police officer.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,888 police officers and military police will be p
osted at all three Zones of Bangkok's Hua Mark Stadium to guard
athletes, VIPs and audiences during the opening and closing
ceremonies to be held on December 6 and 20 respectively, the
source was quoted Friday by the Bangkok Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
Under the security plan, 600 policemen and 20 military police
officers will guard the innermost zone of the stadium where
sports team staff and media members will stand by.
</P>
<P>
On the grandstand, 56 officers will be posted at 29 eastern
entries, 44 at 22 western entries and 24 other at all 12 northern
and southern entries while a group of 24 anti-riot police
officers will oversee rows of seats.
</P>
<P>
Outside the stadium, a total of 85 officers will be posted at
all 26 entries of the stadium. Thirty-one will be at 11 entries
equipped with safety alarms and the others will be at 15 entries
without alarms.
</P>
<P>
A team of 13 police officer with a patrol car and four
motorcycles will also be set up to guard important persons during
stadium ceremonies, he source said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 40 officers will be posted in front of the Indoor
Stadium while 160 and 40 others will be at the stadium's command
center and four gates respectively.
</P>
<P>
A group of two policemen will work at each of 11 ticket
checking points, while 160 officers will be posted around seats
marked for VIPs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
