<HEADLINE> Albania Conducts Military Exercise Near Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Albania conducted a small
military exercise on Thursday in an area bordering Yugoslavia's
autonomous province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Some 650 men of Albania's second infantry division took part
in the two-hour event in the border area known as
Kukes. Fifty-four pieces of artillery, 10 tanks, five 122
milimeter howitzers, anti-aircraft and anti-tank missiles were put
to use.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the division conducted an 11-day drills in the area.
</P>
<P>
Albania Defense Minister Luan Hajdaraga said in a speech
following the exercise that the division and soldiers proved to be
qualified.
</P>
<P>
Major general Kudusi Lamaj, the division commander, said he
hoped the exercise would demonstrate to the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) that the Albanian army continues to enhance
its military ability with a view to working with them and
preventing tensions that threaten the region.
</P>
<P>
"We calmly refrained from a possible war the Serbs attempted to
drag us into," he said. " We believe firmly that it is favorable
to peace."
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo province, which is occupied primarily by Albanians,
has been struggling for independence and a possible merger with
neighboring Albania. 
