<HEADLINE> Albania Police Fight Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Albania police saw achievements
in their latest action combating drug planting and trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian Telegraphic Agency reported that in Sarande
district, police caught three drug traffickers and seized 669
kilograms of marijuana in August. Police said the destination of
these drugs is Greece.
</P>
<P>
In Berat, police destroyed a family marijuana plantation with
about 1,000 marijuana plants.
</P>
<P>
In Vlore, police took immediate action against several villages
which had marijuana plantations and destroyed 9,000 marijuana
plants in three villages. Anti-drug movement is still continuing
in the district. According to police, their aim is to demolish all
the marijuana plantations in the district.
</P>
<P>
Since Albania adopted a policy of reform towards market economy
in 1991, the numbers of both drug addicts and drug trafficking
have been on the rise. Many youngsters, even children, have become
the victims of drugs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
