<HEADLINE> GE Sets up Aircraft Parts Joint Venture in Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 28 (Xinhua) -- General Electric has put into
operation in Xi'an its joint venture in manufacturing aircraft
engine parts with its Chinese partner in the ancient city of
northwest China's Shaanxi province.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, named Asian Aircraft Spare Parts
Manufacturing and Technical Center, is jointly operated by the
Xi'an Aircraft Engine Group Co., Ltd. and General Electric
Aircraft Engines, USA, at a cost of 250 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The center, which is equipped with over 100 advanced production
lines and extensive state-of-the-art equipment, will produce over
5,300 aircraft engine discs and rings annually. The bulk of the
production output will go to General Electric, and the center's
annual output value is expected to hit 40 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an Aircraft Engines, China's largest aircraft engine
manufacturer, and General Electric have established close
cooperative ties over the past decade, with the former currently
producing 30-odd replacement parts for the latter.
</P>
<P>
The Xi'an company delivered more than 2,800 high quality
turbine discs valued at close to 35 million U.S. dollars to
General Electric by the end of July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
