<DOCNO> XIE19980828.0263 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Lowers Price of Medicine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 28 (Xinhua) -- China's medicine retail sales
price has been increasing at a lower rate as a result of the
country's efforts to lower the price of medicine.
</P>
<P>
Previously, medicine retail sales price had been increasing by
10 percent annully, but in the first six months this year it rose
by only 2.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, the country examined and verified all
medicines listed by the central government, both imported and
domestic, and lowered the price of home-produced medicine by 15
per cent, or four billion yuan, and of imported medicine by 10 per
cent, or two billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
There are still problems such as some expensive medicines found
to be of low quality, and some medicine producers who offer high
commissions to those in charge of purchasing medicine for
hospitals.
</P>
<P>
According to officials, money spent for medicine was 51
percent of all the money spent for all medical care services, a
percentage too high for a balance price system.
</P>
<P>
To rationalize the price system, 15 provinces have raised the
cost for medical care services while lowering the price of
medicine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
