<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FC Copenhagen Advance in Cup Winners' Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 27 (Xinhua) -- FC Copenhagen blanked Kraabagh
Agdam of Azerbaijan 4-0 in their European soccer Cup Winners' Cup
qualifying round second leg match on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
With their first leg 6-0 win at home, the Danes secured a
place in the main draw of the competitions at an aggregate
victory of 10-0.
</P>
<P>
Nicklas Jensen and David Newson each scored two goals for the
visitors in Thursday's match.
</P>
<P>
MTK Budapest also hit 10 on aggregate thanks to their 7-0
second leg home victory over Gotu of the Faroe Islands.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarians went into the main draw, winning 10-1.
</P>
<P>
Rapid Bucharest strolled to a 2-0 home win over Luxembourg's
Grevenmacher for an 8-2 aggregate win while Lausanne Sports' 2-1
win at Armenia's Tsement Ararat saw the Swiss advance 7-2 overall.
</P>
<P>
Scottish premier league leaders Hearts thumped Estonian side
Lantana Tallinn 5-0 in Edinburgh for a 6-0 aggregate victory.
</P>
<P>
Partizan Belgrade had to sweat it out for more than an hour
after Dynamo Batumi's Tengiz Sichinava trimmed the Yugos
lavs'aggregate lead to 2-1 in the 28th minute but the Georgians
were unable to grab an equalizer in front of their home fans.
</P>
<P>
In a UEFA Cup second qualifying round, second leg
match,Turkey's Istanbulspor failed to qualify despite beating
Arges Pitesti 4-2 on the night, the Romanians going through on
the away goals rule after winning the first leg 2-0. 
</P>
