<HEADLINE> Cooper, Swoopes and Thompson Head All-WNBA Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Two-time Most Valuable
Player Cynthia Cooper was a unanimous selection to the All-WNBA
first team when the squad was announced today.
</P>
<P>
Two of her teammates from the Houston Comets Tina Thompson and
Sheryl Swoopes also made the team as forwards.
</P>
<P>
The defending champion Comets, preparing for Game One of the
WNBA Finals tonight in Phoenix, were an astounding 27-3 this
season. Cooper averaged a league-high 22.7 points per game and
was seventh in assists at 4.4 per contest. Thompson averaged 12.7
points and 7.1 rebounds in 27 games while Swoopes recorded totals
of 15.6 points, 5.1 rebounds,and 2.1 assists per game.
</P>
<P>
Cooper received 225 points while Swoopes collected
200.Thompson, who repeated her first-team performance of 1997,
garnered 152 points in the voting conducted by a 45-member media
panel.
</P>
<P>
Joining the three on the first team are Phoenix Mercury center
Jennifer Gillom and Cleveland point guard Suzie McConnell Serio,
who also captured New comer of the Year honors.
</P>
<P>
The second team consisted of Los Angeles Sparks center Lisa
Leslie, guards Andrea Stinson of Charlotte and Teresa
Weatherspoon of New York and forwards Eva Nemcova of Cleveland
and Cindy Brown of Detroit. Nemcova and Lieslie were first-team
selections last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
