<HEADLINE> Moldovan Deputy-Prime Minister Visits Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The relations between Romania
and the Republic of Moldova have good prospects, Romanian Foreign
Minister Andrei Plesu said on Thursday, after talks with the
visiting Moldovan deputy-Prime Minister and Minister of Economy
and Reform Ion Sturza.
</P>
<P>
Ion Sturza, who also chairs the Interministerial Committee for
Moldova's relations with Romania arrived Wednesday in Romania on a
three-day official visit, at the invitation of Romanian Foreign
Minister Andrei Plesu, the President of the Interministerial
Committee for the country's relations with Moldova.
</P>
<P>
According to the national Rompres news agency, the
Interministerial Committee's role and activity were examined in the
talks, with special attention on the preparation of the October
meeting of the Interministerial Committees in Moldovan capital
Chisinau.
</P>
<P>
The talks focused on joint targets, and the cooperation in the
power field is one of the most important topics approached,
Romania's chief diplomat said.
</P>
<P>
Ion Sturza is optimistic about the future of ties between his
country and Romania. "We have a legal frame, more than 40
agreements on various levels and, it is very important to start
their implementation more actively. There are a few fields of the
utmost importance, such as the power field," Ion Sturza said. He
added that the Republic of Moldova entirely depended on the
imports of power resources, because it produced only 20 percent of
the consumption power. "We hope to attract strategic investors
from Europe and the USA and we think this will allow us to get
investment funds for a joint market of power resources."
</P>
<P>
The Moldovan guest was received Thursday by Emil
Constantinescu, the President of Romania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
