<HEADLINE> UNSCOM Chief Praises Ritter as "Man of Integrity" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Chief U.N. weapons
inspector Richard Butler on Thursday praised U.S. weapons
inspector Scott Ritter as a "man of integrity.
</P>
<P>
Ritter, who has been with the United Nations Special Commission
(UNSCOM) in charge of dismantling Iraq's weapons of mass
destruction for six years, quitted his post Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters, Butler, Executive Chairman of UNSCOM,
said te resignation letter by Ritter was "a classic in the sense
it gave expression to the strongly held views of a man of
integrity."
</P>
<P>
Butler also said he had no intention of resigning as Executive
Chairman of UNSCOM, as Iraq has demanded, and UNSCOM's work in
Iraq would go on.
</P>
<P>
Ritter, who is in charge of concealment inspection teams in
Iraq, has been accused by Iraq of being a U.S. spy.
</P>
<P>
In his letter of resignation, Ritter accused the U.N.
Secretary-General, the Security Council and the United States of
surrendering to Iraq's whims over the impasse on weapons
inspection.  
</P>
</TEXT>
