<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Arsenic Mitigation-water Supply in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved
Thursday an interest-free credit of 32.4 million U.S. dollars
equivalent for Bangladesh arsenic mitigation-water supply project.
</P>
<P>
Due to high concentrations of arsenic-contaminated water that
is naturally-occurring in thousands of wells across more than half
of Bangladesh's 64 district, this project is designed to support
the country to improve rural and urban infrastructure through
increased access to safe water, especially for the poor and
improve service delivery in health.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be provided by the International Development
Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessional lending arm for
developing countries. 
</P>
