<HEADLINE> Ceausescu's Villas to Become Tourist Attractions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The villas, chalets and
protocol houses of the Ceausescu family will be soon put into
tourist circulation, according to a recent decision taken by the
State Property Public Autonomous Company of Romania which
administrates such places.
</P>
<P>
The Ex-president's famous villas, which lie in Romania's most
beautiful regions in the neighborhood of lakes and fir-tree
forests will become leisure places for foreign holiday-makers who
will pay 3000 - 4000 dollars per night.
</P>
<P>
The villas and palaces in Sinaia, Savirsin, Snagov, Piatra
Neamt, Olanesti, Neptun and hunting chalets in the Carpathians
which are endowed with central heating and other comfortable
facilities will be put into tourist circulation.
</P>
<P>
Before the end of 1989 when Nicolae Ceausescu was out of
power, visiting foreign politicians and states' presidents lived
in some of such luxurious villas. 
</P>
