<HEADLINE> Mortgage Credit Bill Passed to Stimulate House Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian Government passed
on Thursday the bill of mortgage credit, to allow families with
low incomes to get advantageous credit-related building.
</P>
<P>
The newly adopted law indicates that the mortgage credit stands
for the credit granted by financial institutions specializing in
developing, buying, rehabilitation and consolidation of the
buildings for dwelling, commercial and industrial purposes.
</P>
<P>
The mortgage credit can be allotted for at least 10 years for
natural persons and 5 years for legal persons, deadlines to be
extended at request. Any building for which a credit is requested
can be mortgaged along with the plot it is to stand on. In this
case, the mortgage on the plot of land can gradually pass to the
building, during construction.
</P>
<P>
According to the law, the credits can turn into mortgages, if
the customers fail to meet the terms for paying the agreed-on
debts the creditor is entitled to take over the building. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
